<style>
  .article_column-image {
    width: 100%;
    height: 320px;
    border-radius: 11px;
    object-fit: cover;
    object-position: 50% 50%;
  }
  .article_column {
      height: max-content;
  }
  .article_column-third {
    width: calc(33.3333334% - 33.3333334px);
  }
  @media(max-width: 1450px) {
    .article_column-third {
      width: calc(33.3333334% - 20px);
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
      gap: 30px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 1250px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: calc(50% - 15px);
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 750px) {
    .article_column-third {
        width: 100%;
        gap: 30px;
    }
    .article_columns-wrapp {
        gap: 40px;
    }
  }
  @media(max-width: 450px) {
    .article_column-image {
      height: 250px;
    }
  }
</style>

<div class="rebranding_container block-flex-wrap block-gap-50">
  <div class="rebranding-section-title">
    <h2 class="h2-heading-ss">
      Signs your 
      <span class="h2-heading-pp">
        Dior isn’t authentic
      </span>
    </h2>
  </div>
  <div class="article_columns-wrapp block-flex-wrap block-gap-50 block-flex-start-center">
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "dior_sign-1.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Authentic Dior bag interior label and date code">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 1</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Interior label and date code</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Authentic Dior bags have a leather tag inside, usually near the inner zip pocket, embossed with “Christian Dior PARIS made in Italy” or “made in Spain.” Counterfeits often show inconsistent fonts or misspellings. 
          <br><br>
          Dior also includes date codes – combinations of letters and numbers that indicate the production location and date. For example, “01-BO-0129” means February 2019 in Italy. While date codes can help with authentication, counterfeiters may replicate them, so they shouldn’t be the only factor to check.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "dior_sign-2.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Authentic Dior bag stitching quality and patterns">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 2</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Stitching quality and patterns</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          When inspecting the stitching on your Dior item, consistency is crucial. Authentic Dior products have straight, evenly spaced stitches that reflect high-quality craftsmanship. The thread should be strong and match the bag’s color seamlessly. 
          <br><br>
          Iconic patterns like Cannage quilting should align perfectly, with matching patterns at the seams. Counterfeit items often show flaws, such as uneven stitching, mismatched patterns, or visible threads, which do not meet Dior’s high standards of craftsmanship.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="article_column article_column-third block-flex-wrap block-gap-30">
      <img class="article_column-image" src="{{ "dior_sign-3.webp" | asset_url }}" alt="Authentic Dior bag hardware details">
      <div class="article_column-text block-flex-wrap block-gap-15 block-flex-center-center tac">
        <p class="caption w-100">Sign 3</p>
        <h3 class="article_column-title h3-heading-pp w-100">Hardware details</h3>
        <p class="article_column-desc body-text taj w-100">
          Dior’s hardware, such as zippers, clasps, and charms, is made from high-quality metals with precise engravings, reflecting the brand’s craftsmanship. A key sign of authenticity is the clear “CD” engraving on clasps and zippers, which should be crisp and well-defined. 
          <br><br>
          The hardware should feel solid and substantial, adding to the luxury. Counterfeit hardware, however, often feels lighter, may lack engravings, or have poorly executed ones, making it easy to spot a fake.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

{% schema %}
  {
    "name": "Article Three columns",
    "class": "article_columns article_three-columns rebranding-wider-section-bottom rebranding-wider-section-top",
    "settings": []
  }
{% endschema %}